Given the start time of an event in the format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM, compute the end time that is exactly 5 hours later, in the same format. The start time is: {
  "start_time": "2024-05-18 08:00",
  "location": "island trailhead",
  "mark_email": "mark.davies@hotmail.com"
}. Return only the end time string.

Extract the value of the "start_time" field from the following JSON and output it as a plain string. JSON: {
  "start_time": "2024-05-18 08:00",
  "location": "island trailhead",
  "mark_email": "mark.davies@hotmail.com"
}

Extract the value of the "location" field from the following JSON and output it as a plain string. JSON: {
  "start_time": "2024-05-18 08:00",
  "location": "island trailhead",
  "mark_email": "mark.davies@hotmail.com"
}
